race.comment: All but JET represent the Waller yard. SNITZEL MISS (12) rates the best of them. She was narrowly beaten twice at Group level last preparation abd will be better for her two runs this time around. Raced a $2 favourite at Canterbury the latest and Lloyd rides today and will give her every chance from an inside barrier. Waterhouse-Bott-trained JET (3) resumed at Canterbury as a $4 favourite and looked a run short. He'd come off a Randwick trial win and is sure to keep improving. Will jump and run from the inside barrier and will take pegging back. HERMIONE PRANCER (8) resumes and was last seen beaten a whisker at Newcastle on debut. She's trialled sharply for her return and Jason Collett sticks from the latest. Expect her to be right in it. Everything points to improvement from ICHIBAN KOJI (2), who jumps from an inside barrier with a 3kg claim. Last start, he had good support at Randwick-Kensington, and has the blinkers on for the first time.
